The paper discusses the application of artificial intelligence techniques to control production printing equipment, which falls under the category of robotics and automation (cs.RO). The use of AI planning and scheduling algorithms also places it under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and planning and scheduling (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the system's ability to handle execution failures and multi-objective preferences, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the practical application of the system, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
